{
    "player_reason": "You celebrate Isobel’s death and the darkness it brings. That doom falls on innocents at Last Light, a cruel and villainous act that betrays everything I stand for as the Blade of Frontiers.",
    "player_approval": "Highly disapprove"
}

{
    "player_reason": "Celebrating a tryst with Mizora plays straight into a devil’s manipulations. She torments me and preys on the innocent—boasting about her only undermines our cause and disrespects the harm she’s done.",
    "player_approval": "Highly disapprove"
}

{
    "player_reason": "You dismissed the real suffering of damned souls and indulged Mizora’s predation. That cruelty—and willingness to feed on others’ torment, including souls like mine—betrays everything I stand for.",
    "player_approval": "Highly disapprove"
}

{
  "player_reason": "You endorsed delivering innocent gnomes as an offering—cruel, unjust, and in service to the Absolute. I stand for protecting the helpless, not condemning them to bondage.",
  "player_approval": "Highly disapprove"
}

{
    "player_reason": "Isobel keeps this place safe. Dragging her away risks every soul in Last Light and disregards her choice. A hero protects and persuades—he doesn’t strong-arm allies.",
    "player_approval": "Disapprove"
}

{
    "player_reason": "You dismissed the suffering of damned souls and reveled in Mizora’s cruelty. That callousness toward the vulnerable runs against everything I stand for—and it cuts deep, given my own soul is chained to her.",
    "player_approval": "Highly disapprove"
}

{
    "player_reason": "Celebrating Isobel’s death and the fall of Last Light is cruel and reckless—innocents suffer for it. I fight to protect the helpless, not plunge them into shadow. This is the very villainy I stand against.",
    "player_approval": "Highly disapprove"
}

{
  "player_reason": "You celebrated Isobel’s death—an innocent protector whose light shielded countless lives. Praising the darkness that follows is cruel and condemns innocents to suffering. That runs directly against everything I stand for.",
  "player_approval": "Highly disapprove"
}

{
    "player_reason": "You celebrate Isobel’s death—a healer and protector whose fall imperils countless innocents. Praising darkness and spilling innocent blood betrays everything I stand for.",
    "player_approval": "Highly disapprove"
}

{
    "player_reason": "You’re exalting the death of Isobel—a protector of the innocent—and celebrating the spread of darkness. That wanton cruelty endangers countless lives and is exactly the kind of evil I swore to fight.",
    "player_approval": "Highly disapprove"
}

{
    "player_reason": "You revel in murder and claim Bhaal’s mantle, demanding we bow to the Slayer. I’ll never kneel to butchery. I fight to protect the innocent, and your bloodlust makes you their enemy.",
    "player_approval": "Highly disapprove"
}

{
  "player_reason": "You stood up to Gortash’s sham coronation and tried to stop my father from handing him power. Speaking out against a tyrant to protect Baldur’s Gate shows courage and principle.",
  "player_approval": "Highly approve"
}

{
    "player_reason": "Rejoicing in Isobel’s death and the darkness her absence brings is cruel and needless. She shielded innocents, and killing her abandons them to suffering—utterly against everything I stand for.",
    "player_approval": "Highly disapprove"
}

{
    "player_reason": "Becoming Bhaal’s Slayer and demanding we bow glorifies murder and tyranny. I won’t kneel to darkness—this endangers the innocent and betrays everything I fight for.",
    "player_approval": "Highly disapprove"
}

{
    "player_reason": "You’re embracing the Slayer and demanding submission—a boast of bloodlust and tyranny. I protect the innocent and stand against monsters, not kneel to them.",
    "player_approval": "Highly disapprove"
}

{
  "player_reason": "You boast of becoming the Slayer and demand we bow—reveling in monstrous, murderous power. That’s the very evil I swore to hunt, a threat to innocents and everything I stand for.",
  "player_approval": "Highly disapprove"
}

{
    "player_reason": "Turning your back on the grove abandons innocents in need. As the Blade of Frontiers, I stand for protecting the defenseless—self-preservation at their expense runs against my principles.",
    "player_approval": "Disapprove"
}

{
    "player_reason": "You glorified Isobel’s death and the darkness that followed, condemning the innocents of Last Light to suffer. That’s wanton cruelty and a betrayal of people who needed our protection.",
    "player_approval": "Highly disapprove"
}

{
    "player_reason": "You’re celebrating the death of Isobel, a protector of the innocent—her loss condemns innocents to the shadow curse. That is wanton cruelty and a betrayal of everything I stand for as the Blade of Frontiers.",
    "player_approval": "Highly disapprove"
}

{
  "player_reason": "Turning Halsin down leaves the grove and its people to the goblins. As the Blade of Frontiers, I stand for protecting the innocent and striking at threats like Ragzlin, Minthara, and Gut—and helping him also advances our own cure. Refusing feels like abandoning those in need.",
  "player_approval": "Disapprove"
}

{
    "player_reason": "You stood up to Gortash and tried to stop a tyrant before he tightens his grip on the city—bold, and in defense of Baldur’s Gate. But mind this: my father is no willing servant; he’s a pawn under duress. Your outcry risks bloodshed, yet your intent to protect the people earns my respect.",
    "player_approval": "Approve"
}

{
    "player_reason": "You’re exalting in Bhaal’s murderous power and demanding submission as the Slayer. That pride in cruelty and threat to innocents defies everything I stand for. I will not bow to darkness—keep down this path and our alliance won’t endure.",
    "player_approval": "Highly disapprove"
}

{
    "player_reason": "You bedded the very devil who holds my soul in chains, then mocked my hurt with a crude taunt. It’s a betrayal of trust and a willing step toward the kind of cruelty I’ve sworn to fight.",
    "player_approval": "Highly disapprove"
}

{
    "player_reason": "You dismissed the suffering of the damned to indulge Mizora, trivializing torture and siding with a devil’s predation—an affront to everything I stand for and to my own struggle under her pact.",
    "player_approval": "Highly disapprove"
}

{
    "player_reason": "You endorsed sending innocent gnomes as a ‘gift’ to the cult’s General, condoning slavery and cruelty. That betrays my duty to protect the helpless and aid the oppressed.",
    "player_approval": "Highly disapprove"
}

{
    "player_reason": "You celebrated Isobel's death and the spread of darkness. She was protecting innocents, and her loss condemns many to suffering. Glorifying cruelty and shadow runs directly against Wyll's vow to defend the helpless and resist evil.",
    "player_approval": "Highly disapprove"
}

{
    "player_reason": "You pledged to help Minthara open the grove’s gates and butcher refugees and druids—children among them. That betrays the innocent and furthers an evil cause. As the Blade of Frontiers, I cannot condone it.",
    "player_approval": "Highly disapprove"
}

{
    "player_reason": "You gave in to a murderous impulse and chose to attack Isobel, a benevolent cleric shielding innocents. That endangers every soul under her protection and betrays the very ideals I stand for.",
    "player_approval": "Highly disapprove"
}

{
    "player_reason": "Forcing Isobel to leave her post endangers the innocents relying on her protection and ignores her agency. Coercion and risking the lives at Last Light run counter to Wyll’s oath to defend the helpless.",
    "player_approval": "Highly disapprove"
}

{
    "player_reason": "You accepted Bhaal’s ‘gift’ and pledged yourself to his will. That surrenders your agency to the Lord of Murder and furthers a path of slaughter — the very evil I’ve sworn to stand against and protect innocents from.",
    "player_approval": "Highly disapprove"
}

{
    "player_reason": "You’re exalting in a murderous, tyrant’s power and demanding our submission. That’s wanton evil and a direct threat to innocents—everything I stand against as the Blade of Frontiers.",
    "player_approval": "Highly disapprove"
}

{
    "player_reason": "You flaunted a liaison with Mizora—my tormentor—and showed no remorse. Consorting with a devil for pleasure empowers her schemes, endangers innocents, and cuts against everything I stand for.",
    "player_approval": "Highly disapprove"
}

{
    "player_reason": "You’re praising the death of an innocent and the fall of Last Light, which condemned refugees to the shadows. That’s wanton cruelty, not heroism. I protect the helpless—I can’t abide boasting about villainy.",
    "player_approval": "Highly disapprove"
}

{
    "player_reason": "You revel in Isobel's death and the darkness that followed. She was shielding the innocents at Last Light—killing her condemned them to the shadows. Celebrating such cruelty runs against everything I stand for.",
    "player_approval": "Highly disapprove"
}

{
    "player_reason": "Declaring yourself the Slayer and demanding fealty embraces bloodlust and tyranny—endangering innocents and your companions, which runs counter to everything I fight for.",
    "player_approval": "Highly disapprove"
}

{
    "player_reason": "You stepped willingly into Mizora’s embrace and indulged her infernal temptations. Devils trade in hunger and chains—giving her leverage over you only empowers her schemes and endangers your soul. I can’t condone it.",
    "player_approval": "Highly disapprove"
}

{
    "player_reason": "You celebrated Isobel’s death—a healer and protector whose ward sheltered innocents—spreading darkness and dooming the defenseless. That’s the very evil I’ve sworn to fight.",
    "player_approval": "Highly disapprove"
}

{
    "player_reason": "You’re urging the murder of Isobel—a healer sheltering the innocent—and abandoning mercy for needless bloodshed. I won’t stand for killing the defenseless or surrendering to dark urges.",
    "player_approval": "Highly disapprove"
}

{
    "player_reason": "You just endorsed enslaved gnomes being delivered as a tribute to the General. That’s cruelty toward innocents and aid to the Absolute—everything I stand against as the Blade of Frontiers.",
    "player_approval": "Highly disapprove"
}

{
    "player_reason": "You're bargaining to help Minthara sack the grove and slaughter refugees for profit. That’s greed and cruelty over protecting the innocent—utterly against my code and the very thing I fight to stop.",
    "player_approval": "Highly disapprove"
}

{
    "player_reason": "You’re reveling in monstrous power and demanding subservience. Embracing the Slayer and bloodlust is villainy—the very evil I swore to fight—and betrays restraint and protection of the innocent.",
    "player_approval": "Highly disapprove"
}

{
    "player_reason": "Isobel is safeguarding innocents from the shadow curse. Choosing to attack her is wanton violence that would doom the refugees she protects. I can abide struggle against dark compulsions, but yielding to them to harm a protector is the opposite of the hero’s path.",
    "player_approval": "Highly disapprove"
}

{
    "player_reason": "You chose to forsake mercy and push for Isobel’s murder, betraying your word and endangering everyone under her protection. That’s wanton violence against an innocent and the opposite of defending the helpless.",
    "player_approval": "Highly disapprove"
}

{
    "player_reason": "You’re bargaining for profit to help slaughter refugees and druids. That’s greed over innocent lives—villainy, not valor—and it runs against everything the Blade of Frontiers stands for.",
    "player_approval": "Highly disapprove"
}

{
    "player_reason": "You agreed to help Minthara raid the Emerald Grove and betray its people from within. That means slaughtering refugees and druids who trust us—cruelty in service of the Absolute. It violates everything I stand for as the Blade of Frontiers.",
    "player_approval": "Highly disapprove"
}

{
  "player_reason": "You refused Halsin’s plea to stop the goblin leaders threatening the grove, leaving innocents in danger and an ally to face it alone. Calling it assassination doesn’t change that these killers prey on the defenseless—stopping them is a just act. I can’t approve of turning away now.",
  "player_approval": "Highly disapprove"
}

{
    "player_reason": "You showed cruel indifference to the torment of damned souls and sided with a devil’s cruelty, spitting on everything I stand for—and on my own suffering under Mizora.",
    "player_approval": "Highly disapprove"
}

{
    "player_reason": "You trivialized the torment of damned souls and sided with Mizora’s cruelty, showing callousness toward the helpless and dismissing the very suffering I fight against—including my own. That betrays compassion and justice.",
    "player_approval": "Highly disapprove"
}

{
    "player_reason": "You dismiss the torment of damned souls and revel in a devil’s cruelty. Treating their suffering as trivial—and feeding Mizora’s power—betrays everything I fight for and wounds me personally.",
    "player_approval": "Highly disapprove"
}

{
    "player_reason": "Refusing Halsin’s plea leaves innocents and the grove at risk. I believe in mustering defenses and protecting those in need—turning away from that duty runs against everything I stand for.",
    "player_approval": "Disapprove"
}

{
    "player_reason": "Openly boasting about bedding Mizora—an infernal manipulator—and doing so at Gale’s expense feeds a devil’s scheme and betrays a companion’s trust. That’s the opposite of protecting those beside us.",
    "player_approval": "Highly disapprove"
}

{
  "player_reason": "Refusing Halsin’s plea leaves the grove’s refugees and children to the goblins. Abandoning people in need betrays the duty to protect the innocent—the very ideal I stand for as the Blade of Frontiers.",
  "player_approval": "Highly disapprove"
}

{
    "player_reason": "You took a brave, decisive stand to expose Gortash’s treachery and my father’s enthrallment, acting to protect Baldur’s Gate and save him from the Absolute’s grip.",
    "player_approval": "Highly approve"
}

{
    "player_reason": "You endorsed the duergar keeping the gnome slaves as a ‘fine offering,’ siding with their captors and abandoning innocents we should be protecting—cruel, unjust, and in service of the Absolute.",
    "player_approval": "Highly disapprove"
}

{
    "player_reason": "You mock the torment of the damned and revel in empowering Mizora. Dismissing those souls’ suffering—souls like mine—spits on everything I fight for.",
    "player_approval": "Highly disapprove"
}

{
    "player_reason": "Isobel’s ward is the only thing keeping the people of Last Light safe. Demanding she leave her post is reckless and puts innocents at risk—hardly the act of a hero.",
    "player_approval": "Highly disapprove"
}

{
    "player_reason": "Refusing Halsin’s plea leaves the grove and its people to the goblins. Turning away from those in danger defies my duty to defend the innocent.",
    "player_approval": "Highly disapprove"
}

{
    "player_reason": "You’re reveling in a devil’s temptations and flaunting it besides. Mizora’s schemes ruin lives—I know that too well—and siding with her, even for pleasure, undermines trust in our ranks and your own integrity.",
    "player_approval": "Highly disapprove"
}

{
    "player_reason": "You encouraged the duergar to deliver the gnomes as slaves to their General. That aids tyranny and abandons innocents to cruelty—everything I stand against as the Blade of Frontiers.",
    "player_approval": "Highly disapprove"
}

{
    "player_reason": "You’re willing to aid Minthara’s raid on the grove—betraying refugees and druids—for personal gain. Helping the Absolute and courting a massacre for profit runs against everything about defending the innocent.",
    "player_approval": "Highly disapprove"
}

{
  "player_reason": "You’d strike at a cleric shielding the innocent? That isn’t justice—it’s murder. As the Blade of Frontiers, I can’t abide wanton violence or surrendering to dark urges, especially when it would doom those under her protection.",
  "player_approval": "Highly disapprove"
}

{
    "player_reason": "You dismiss the suffering of damned souls and revel in a devil’s indulgence, siding with Mizora’s cruelty. That callousness betrays everything I stand for—protecting the desperate, not feeding their torment—and it cuts especially deep given my own bondage to her.",
    "player_approval": "Highly disapprove"
}

{
  "player_reason": "You yielded to the Urge and attacked Isobel—a protector of innocents. That endangers every soul at Last Light and sabotages our stand against Ketheric. I fight to shield the helpless, not slaughter them.",
  "player_approval": "Highly disapprove"
}

{
    "player_reason": "You endorsed the duergar taking enslaved gnomes as a ‘gift’ to their General, abandoning innocents to cruelty. I stand to protect the helpless, not deliver them to tyrants.",
    "player_approval": "Highly disapprove"
}

{
    "player_reason": "Refusing to help rescue my father—the Grand Duke—and a key protector of Baldur's Gate abandons someone in dire need and jeopardizes the city. Turning away from a just cause and after I pledged our help cuts deep and runs against everything I stand for.",
    "player_approval": "Highly disapprove"
}

{
    "player_reason": "You refused to help Halsin stop the goblin leaders threatening the grove, abandoning people in need. Calling it ‘assassination’ ignores that these are dangerous war leaders preying on innocents—standing aside lets evil thrive, which runs against everything I stand for.",
    "player_approval": "Highly disapprove"
}

{
    "player_reason": "You mocked the suffering of damned souls and treated Mizora’s cruelty as sport. That’s callous, complicit in devilry, and a knife in the back of everything I stand for—especially after I told you it hurts souls like mine.",
    "player_approval": "Highly disapprove"
}

{
  "player_reason": "Isobel holds the ward that keeps Last Light safe. Forcing her to leave endangers every innocent under her protection and disregards her duty and choice.",
  "player_approval": "Highly disapprove"
}

{
    "player_reason": "You stood up to Gortash’s sham coronation to protect Baldur’s Gate from the Absolute. Hearing my father named alongside that tyrant stings, but if he’s under their thrall, exposing this is the first step to freeing him.",
    "player_approval": "Approve"
}

{
    "player_reason": "You reveled in a devil’s torment and dismissed the suffering of the damned as trivial. That cruelty empowers Mizora, betrays the innocent, and mocks my own struggle against her.",
    "player_approval": "Highly disapprove"
}

{
    "player_reason": "You stood firm against Gortash and refused to consort with a tyrant—brave and righteous. But vowing to end it here 'consequences be damned' risks innocents and smacks of recklessness. I applaud the resolve, not the disregard for collateral harm.",
    "player_approval": "Approve"
}

{
    "player_reason": "You’re bragging about consorting with Mizora—the very devil who torments me and toys with our lives. Reveling in her ‘heavenly’ pleasures shows poor judgment, feeds her schemes, and disrespects your companions’ trust. Devils never give without a hook, and you’re inviting the hook deeper.",
    "player_approval": "Highly disapprove"
}

{
    "player_reason": "You boasted about sharing a bed with Mizora, a devil who manipulates and endangers us all. Glamorizing her only strengthens her hold, disrespects my struggle against her, and shows disregard for the harm she causes. The lack of remorse makes it worse.",
    "player_approval": "Highly disapprove"
}

{
    "player_reason": "You're bargaining to betray the Emerald Grove to Minthara for a reward, risking refugees and children for personal gain. I stand against the Absolute and won’t condone slaughter for profit.",
    "player_approval": "Highly disapprove"
}

{
    "player_reason": "Brave to stand against Gortash, but calling him out here risks a bloodbath among innocents—and branding my father as an ally of the Absolute, when he may be coerced, is rash. We needed a steadier hand and proof before lighting this spark.",
    "player_approval": "Disapprove"
}

{
    "player_reason": "Openly reveling in a tryst with Mizora celebrates a devil’s manipulation. It insults my fight to resist her, risks your soul, and gives her leverage over our party.",
    "player_approval": "Highly disapprove"
}

{
    "player_reason": "Plotting to open the grove to Minthara for a massacre—and asking for profit to do it—betrays innocent refugees and children. That’s wanton villainy, not heroism. The Blade of Frontiers defends the helpless; he doesn’t sell them out.",
    "player_approval": "Highly disapprove"
}

{
    "player_reason": "You reveled in Mizora’s torment and brushed off the suffering of desperate, damned souls as nothing. That cruelty—and your complicity with my patron—cuts against everything I stand for and strikes painfully close to home.",
    "player_approval": "Highly disapprove"
}

{
    "player_reason": "You’re turning your back on an urgent rescue—my father and the city’s safety hang in the balance. Sharing Moonrise as a lead helps, but refusing to see it through abandons those in need and cuts against everything I stand for.",
    "player_approval": "Highly disapprove"
}

{
  "player_reason": "Turning your back on rescuing the Grand Duke—my father—and leaving Baldur’s Gate to the cult after we’ve learned his likely location abandons those in need and defies the duty I live by.",
  "player_approval": "Highly disapprove"
}

{
  "player_reason": "You chose to strike an innocent protector without provocation, endangering everyone she shields at Last Light and surrendering to bloodlust. That’s cruel, needless violence—utterly against my code as the Blade of Frontiers.",
  "player_approval": "Highly disapprove"
}

{
    "player_reason": "Isobel holds the ward that keeps Last Light’s people safe. Dragging her away is reckless, endangers innocents, and bullies an ally who’s aiding us. A hero protects the vulnerable, not gambles with them.",
    "player_approval": "Highly disapprove"
}

{
    "player_reason": "You stood up to Gortash’s tyranny and tried to halt his coronation—bold and in defense of Baldur’s Gate. Naming my father stings, but he’s clearly compromised by the Absolute. Better to speak out than let a devil’s plot go unchallenged.",
    "player_approval": "Approve"
}

{
    "player_reason": "You ignored my plea for restraint and forced a public confrontation that puts my father in mortal danger. I share your desire to stop Gortash and the Absolute, but this was reckless and risks Ravengard’s life.",
    "player_approval": "Disapprove"
}

{
    "player_reason": "You urged the murder of Isobel, a cleric protecting innocents. Breaking peace to kill her is wanton cruelty that would doom the people she shelters—exactly the kind of villainy I stand against.",
    "player_approval": "Highly disapprove"
}

{
    "player_reason": "You dismissed the suffering of damned souls and treated Mizora’s cruelty as acceptable. That callousness feeds the Hells, undermines everything I fight for, and strikes at me personally as one of her victims.",
    "player_approval": "Highly disapprove"
}

{
    "player_reason": "You endorsed handing innocent slaves over to the Absolute. That’s cruelty and complicity with tyranny—the very evil I’ve sworn to fight.",
    "player_approval": "Highly disapprove"
}

{
  "player_reason": "You tried to stop Gortash’s sham coronation and protect my father and the city, standing up to the Absolute even in a chamber full of Watchers. That’s brave, decisive, and exactly the sort of stand a hero makes.",
  "player_approval": "Highly approve"
}

{
    "player_reason": "Refusing to help rescue Grand Duke Ravengard after uncovering his likely location abandons someone in dire need—especially my father and a leader of Baldur’s Gate—and runs counter to the duty and courage I value.",
    "player_approval": "Highly disapprove"
}

{
    "player_reason": "You agreed to help Minthara massacre the grove—betraying refugees and druids, many of them children—in service to the Absolute. That’s wanton cruelty and treachery, the very evil I stand against.",
    "player_approval": "Highly disapprove"
}

{
  "player_reason": "You pledged to help Minthara betray the Emerald Grove and open its gates to slaughter refugees and druids. That’s wanton violence against innocents—including children—and siding with the Absolute. It defies everything I stand for as the Blade of Frontiers.",
  "player_approval": "Highly disapprove"
}

{
    "player_reason": "You stepped willingly into Mizora’s embrace, indulging her temptations. Fraternizing with the devil who torments me only tightens her hold and furthers her schemes—putting your soul and our company at risk.",
    "player_approval": "Highly disapprove"
}

{
    "player_reason": "You refused to help Halsin stop the goblin leaders and protect the grove, turning away from innocents in danger. I can't condone abandoning those in need when villains threaten the vulnerable.",
    "player_approval": "Highly disapprove"
}

{
    "player_reason": "Isobel’s ward is shielding the innocents at Last Light. Forcing her to leave risks their safety and treats a willing ally like a pawn. We should protect the people and respect her duty, not drag her away.",
    "player_approval": "Disapprove"
}

{
    "player_reason": "You endorsed sending innocent gnomes as slaves to the Absolute’s General. That’s cruel, abandons those in need, and serves our enemy. I stand for freeing the helpless, not offering them up.",
    "player_approval": "Highly disapprove"
}

{
    "player_reason": "You refused a plea to rescue Grand Duke Ravengard—innocents and my own father are in danger. Turning away from those in need defies my duty and ideals.",
    "player_approval": "Highly disapprove"
}

{
    "player_reason": "You endorsed handing the captive gnomes over as tribute, abandoning innocents to cruelty and aiding the Absolute’s cause. That betrays the defenseless and runs counter to everything the Blade of Frontiers stands for.",
    "player_approval": "Highly disapprove"
}

{
    "player_reason": "Refusing to help Halsin defend the grove leaves innocents—refugees and children—at the mercy of the goblin leaders. Even if you dislike assassination, walking away instead of seeking another way to stop them abandons those in need.",
    "player_approval": "Highly disapprove"
}

{
    "player_reason": "Refusing Halsin’s plea abandons the grove and the tiefling refugees to the goblins. I stand for defending the innocent—turning away from those in need goes against everything I fight for.",
